        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(agents): strip reasoning tags from chat replies",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #89473.\n\n- Treat `<reasoning>` and `<antml:reasoning>` as reasoning-control tags in the shared final assistant text sanitizer.\n- Align the embedded stream/block-reply tag matcher and message recompute trigger so chat-channel streaming delivery strips those tags too, including split opener fragments and attribute-bearing openers.\n- Add focused sanitizer, `extractAssistantText`, and subscriber regressions for regular, namespaced, split, and attribute-bearing reasoning tags.\n\n## Root Cause\n\nThe OpenAI-compatible stream partitioner already recognized `reasoning` tags, but the final sanitizer and embedded stream delivery matchers only covered think/thinking/thought variants. That left `<reasoning>...</reasoning>` text able to survive final assistant extraction or chat block-reply delivery. Split opener fragments could leak when the stream buffered only the older tag names, and attribute-bearing openers could still be missed by the embedded stream scanner even though the shared sanitizer accepted attributes.\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\nBehavior addressed: Assistant-visible final text and embedded chat block-reply streaming now strip hidden `<reasoning>` and `<antml:reasoning>` blocks through the same reasoning-tag taxonomy used for existing think/thinking tags, including when opening tags are split across stream chunks or carry attributes.\n\nReal environment tested: Local OpenClaw checkout on this PR branch at `80122cae81`, running the source `extractAssistantText` path and real `subscribeEmbeddedAgentSession` block-reply subscriptions with `blockReplyBreak: \"text_end\"`.\n\nExact steps or command run after this patch: Ran a local `pnpm exec tsx --eval` command that imported `src/agents/embedded-agent-utils.ts` and `src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.ts`, extracted assistant text from `Before <reasoning hidden=\"1\">hidden draft</reasoning> After`, then streamed `<reasoning hidden=\"1\">hidden stream` + `</reasoning>\\n\\nVisible reply` and `<antml:reasoning hidden=\"1\">hidden stream` + `</antml:reasoning>\\n\\nVisible reply` through subscribed embedded sessions and collected `onBlockReply` output.\n\nEvidence after fix: Console output from the direct run:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"extractAssistantText\": \"Before  After\",\n  \"reasoningAttributeBlockReplies\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \"Visible reply\",\n      \"audioAsVoice\": false,\n      \"replyToTag\": false,\n      \"replyToCurrent\": false\n    }\n  ],\n  \"antmlReasoningAttributeBlockReplies\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \"Visible reply\",\n      \"audioAsVoice\": false,\n      \"replyToTag\": false,\n      \"replyToCurrent\": false\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nObserved result after fix: The hidden reasoning payloads were absent from extracted assistant text and from both attribute-bearing chat block replies. The only chat-visible block reply text was `Visible reply`.\n\nWhat was not tested: Full repository suite, broad changed checks, GitHub CI beyond the checks GitHub ran for this PR, and live MiniMax/LiteLLM reproduction.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm exec tsx --eval '...'` direct extraction + subscriber attribute-bearing block-reply proof above\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/shared/text/reasoning-tags.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-utils.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.subscribe-embedded-agent-session.subscribeembeddedagentsession.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.handlers.messages.test.ts --reporter=dot` -> 4 files / 202 tests passed\n- `pnpm exec oxfmt --check src/shared/text/reasoning-tags.ts src/shared/text/reasoning-tags.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-utils.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-utils.test.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.e2e-harness.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.handlers.messages.ts src/agents/embedded-agent-subscribe.subscribe-embedded-agent-session.subscribeembeddedagentsession.test.ts` -> passed\n- `git diff --check` -> passed",
        "branch": "codex/fix-reasoning-tag-leak",
